==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: honey creeper
<hw>honey creeper</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Any of a number of small to medium-sized finches of the
Hawaiian islands belonging to the subfamily
<fam>Drepanidae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Hawaiian honeycreeper.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>any of numerous species of small, bright, colored,
passerine birds of the family <fam>C⟦oe⟧rebid⟦ae⟧</fam>, related to the
tanagers and wood warblers, abundant in Central and South America; they
are songbirds with a curved bill for sucking nectar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honeydew</ent>⟦br⟧
